    "MissionGiver": "ArcCorp",
    "Title": "RESOURCE DRIVE: RECOVER LARGE SHIPMENT",
    "TitleKey": "GoblinG_ArcCorp_RecoverCargo_L_Title",
    "Description": "Hey, it\u2019s El.\n\nWe\u2019ve got a situation over at <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4>. One of our contractors who was in the middle of transporting a lot of cargo for us stopped returning our comms. Hopefully it\u2019s just a glitch, but being realistic, it\u2019s probably something much worse. While that sucks and I feel bad, we all still got deadlines, right?\n\nAnyway, we want you to head out with a large hauling vessel and grab their shipment of cargo. It\u2019ll be pretty big so I\u2019d definitely make sure you pack your <EM4>heavy-duty tractor beam</EM4> and <EM4>bring someone reliable</EM4> to help you out. Expect to find between <EM4>100-125 SCU</EM4> of various box sizes.\n\nTake it to a freight elevator at: <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address|ListAll)</EM4>. I\u2019ll make sure someone\u2019s on site to take care of it. We\u2019ll pay you a proportional amount for whatever you\u2019re able to return.\n\nIf you don\u2019t have a big enough ship, you could always fly the abandoned cargo ship back. Though, you\u2019d have to bring another pilot with you unless you plan on leaving your ship behind.\n\nHope you have better luck than the original haulers did.\n\n\nElla Tieno\nContractor Liaison Officer\nArcCorp",
    "DescriptionKey": "GoblinG_ArcCorp_RecoverCargo_L_Desc",
    "DisplayDescription": "Hey, it\u2019s El.\n\nWe\u2019ve got a situation over at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>. One of our contractors who was in the middle of transporting a lot of cargo for us stopped returning our comms. Hopefully it\u2019s just a glitch, but being realistic, it\u2019s probably something much worse. While that sucks and I feel bad, we all still got deadlines, right?\n\nAnyway, we want you to head out with a large hauling vessel and grab their shipment of cargo. It\u2019ll be pretty big so I\u2019d definitely make sure you pack your <EM4>heavy-duty tractor beam</EM4> and <EM4>bring someone reliable</EM4> to help you out. Expect to find between <EM4>100-125 SCU</EM4> of various box sizes.\n\nTake it to a freight elevator at: <EM4>Area18</EM4>. I\u2019ll make sure someone\u2019s on site to take care of it. We\u2019ll pay you a proportional amount for whatever you\u2019re able to return.\n\nIf you don\u2019t have a big enough ship, you could always fly the abandoned cargo ship back. Though, you\u2019d have to bring another pilot with you unless you plan on leaving your ship behind.\n\nHope you have better luck than the original haulers did.\n\n\nElla Tieno\nContractor Liaison Officer\nArcCorp",
